        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 5:20AM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 520 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking gusty showers along a line
extending from 3 miles northwest of Waynesville to 7 miles south of
Sylva to 3 miles northeast of Hiawassee. Movement was east at 40
mph. An isolated thunderstorm could develop along the line.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dillsboro, Franklin, Tuckasegee, Cruso, Wolf Mountain, B.R.
Parkway-Black Balsam To Mount Pisgah, Scaly Mountain, Sylva,
Cullowhee, and B.R. Parkway-Balsam Gap To Black Balsam Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM EDT for western North
Carolina.</instruction>
